Package: hrsample
Title: A Sample Human Resources Database for Educational Purposes
Version: 0.0.0.5003
Authors@R: person("Harry", "Ahlas", email = "hahlas@hotmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: The hrsample database is a series of seven tables of human resources data for an imaginary company. The database's fully reproducible code is available at https://github.com/harryahlas/sample-hr-database/.  Please note the data will change in future versions.  Current tables include employeeinfo_table, deskhistory_table, deskjob_table, hierarchy_table, performancereview_table, recruiting_table, salaryhistory_table, recruiting_table, contact_table, education_table, skills_table. A hierarchical view called rollup_view is also available.  See R/data.R for more information.  May refer to http://harry.ahlas.com for tutorials.  Package includes functions to load tables to MySQL, PostgreSQL, SQLite, and SQL Server databases.
Depends: R (>= 3.4.4)
Suggests:
	DBI,
	odbc,
	RMySQL,
	RPostgreSQL,
	RSQLite
License: CC0
URL: https://github.com/harryahlas/hrsample 
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 6.1.0.9000
